cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.CL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image-based features and word-level geometric differences between fonts. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of font identification to improve OCR systems and mass digitization projects. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper presents an active-learning strategy to reduce the number of labeled samples needed to train a font classifier. 
- cs.DL (Deep Learning) is possible as the paper may use deep learning techniques for feature extraction or classification. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible as the paper deals with text transcription and font identification, which are related to natural language processing.
